                <para>Recent studies of axle shaft flange gasket leakage has indicated that leakage is caused by loss of
                    axle flange fastener clamp load and not the flange gasket material.
                </para>
                <para>As a result of this study the axle flange mounting hardware has been changed in production. The
                    flange mounting nuts have been changed to Grade 8 (Figure 1) and utilize hardened flat washers. The
                    tightening torque has been revised for improved clamp load at the flange joint. Refer to Table 3.
                </para>
                <para>Axles that use cone lock type axle shafts do not require the use of hardened washers and should be
                    tightened to the Grade 5 torque specification listed in Table 4.
                </para>
                <para></para>
                <para>When performing a Pre-Delivery Inspection (PDI), it is important that the new fasteners be
                    tightened to the torque values in Table 3. The PDI Manual has been updated to the new torque values.
                </para>
                <para>The New Vehicle Processing Manual has also been updated to reflect the new flange hardware and
                    torque values.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <caution>
                        <para>It is important that the axle flange mounting hardware be tightened to the new torque
                            value in Table 3 before the vehicle is driven.
                        </para>
                    </caution>
                </specpara>
                <para>
                    <title>Models Built Before The Axle Flange Hardware Change</title>
                </para>
                <para>The models listed above and built before the Start Date shown, that have flange gasket leakage can
                    be retrofitted with the new flange mounting hardware listed in the
                    <emph type="bold">Parts Information Table 2.</emph>
                </para>
                <para>If a single axle flange requires the replacement four (4) or more old style flange nuts, all the
                    nuts should be replaced with Grade 8 nuts and hardened washers. Refer to Table 3 for the torque
                    specification.
                </para>
                <para>If a single axle flange requires the replacement of three (3) or less old style flange nuts,
                    install the new Grade 8 nut and hardened washer only where needed and refer to Table 4 for the
                    torque specification.
                </para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
